He referred to the meetings that Secretary of State Marco Rubio and other US officials had with Russian officials last week in Saudi Arabia. "Our goal is to achieve a ceasefire as soon as possible and ultimately a permanent peace," Trump said at the joint press conference with Macron.
Trump said that "the United States has provided Ukraine with more aid than any other nation." He said that the United States sent about 300 billion dollars to Ukraine and that Europe sent about 100."It's a big difference," Trump added. "We should level it. But let's hope we don't have to worry about this, we have other things going on that maybe they will take him out of the kingdom of necessity." Trump said that most of Europe's contribution came in the form of loans to Ukraine, while that of the United States came in the form of grants. "The United States also deserves to recover the massive sums of money we sent."
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
Trump paid tribute to the third anniversary of Russia's large-scale invasion of Ukraine, apparently recognizing that it was an invasion after speculating last week that Ukraine had "initiated" the war. "The invasion of Ukraine would never have happened if you were president," he said. "It wouldn't have happened." Trump added that "million people die every week." "Thousands of thousands of people, particularly Russian and Ukrainian, died unnecessarily," he said.
