Putin will accept the presence of European peacekeepers in Ukraine. The President of the United States, Donald Trump, who is meeting at the White House French President Macron.
These declarations, if confirmed, would mean a change in Moscow's position, which so far has considered the sending of European troops to Ukraine as a "red line" and an aggression by Europe.<br> In an exchange of jokes with journalists, Trump was asked if Putin would accept the presence of European troops in Ukraine, and he answered: "He'll accept it." He later stated that he had discussed the matter with the Russian leader who would express his approval. "If we reach this agreement to end the war, he will no longer seek wars. I asked him specifically and he has no problem with this," said Trump.<br> The United Kingdom and France are driving efforts to create a "European redistribution force" to prevent future Russian attacks against cities, ports and critical infrastructure in Ukraine, if a peace agreement was reached by the United States.<br> According to Western officials cited by the Guardian, the proposal would involve the use of less than 30,000 soldiers, mainly focused on air and sea defense. The presence of ground forces would be minimal and would not be located near the front line in eastern Ukraine, where Russia occupies territories. The same Macron, last Thursday, opened the door to sending peacekeeping forces in Ukraine "in the framework of a planned framework", once peace in the country was negotiated. Also British Prime Minister Keir Starmer, who will meet Trump on Thursday, declared himself in favour of the study of this option, which enjoys the support of some Baltic countries, such as Sweden.&nbsp;
<h2>Not on the contrary of a Ukrainian state
Russia has nothing against the maintenance of the Ukrainian state, but Ukraine should not be used as a hostile launch pad. Russian President Vladimir Putin said this, answering the questions of VGTRK journalist Pavel Zarubin.<br> The Head of State has emphasized that Russia is interested in Ukraine becoming, ultimately, a neighbouring country friend. "The position, as it seems to me, of the President of the United States is not linked to the fact that this is in our interest, in that of Russia. It is most likely in the interest of Ukraine, the Ukrainian State, with the aim of preserving Ukrainian statues. We have nothing against this. Although, of course, we would like this territory not to be used as a launch pad for attacks on the Russian Federation, it was not used as a hostile launch pad for us. In order to eventually turn into a neighbouring country," said the Head of the Russian State
