<div </div
On the urgency of a new government, the president of the industrial group Bdi, Peter Leibinger, said on Sunday the urgent need for the German economy of an executive "who can act very quickly". In the party's seat, in front of journalists, Merz immediately analyzed and commented the incredible growth of AfD - an extreme right-wing party arrived second with 20.8 percent, sending a message to all traditional German political forces.
